data.description: This is a beautiful Central Point property with privacy and seclusion, nestled between Upper and Lower Table Rocks.  There are 3 lots, with a total of 10.02 acres, and all zoned EFU.  The main house is 3 bedrooms, 2 baths, 2 car garage with 1676 square feet, with a light and bright open floorplan.  It is a single level ranch style home with a metal roof, and has beautiful pasture and valley views.   There is a 24' by 50' shop with power (220), a 3 stall barn with hay storage, and a 27' by 35' meat shop with walk in cooler that also has power.  The meat cutting area has a hook in the ceiling and a band saw built in for butchering.  There is a greenhouse behind the barn and a wood shed for wood storage.  The property has 3 wells, and is fenced and cross fenced.  The main house lot has 1.32 acres, the second lot has 3.68 acres and the third lot has 5.02 acres. This is the first time this beautiful country home just minutes to town has been offered for sale.  It is a must tour property.
